Intermediate Algebra_Level 2_1.json.problem:
A polynomial with integer coefficients is of the form
\[x^3 + a_2 x^2 + a_1 x - 11 = 0.\]Enter all the possible integer roots of this polynomial, separated by commas.
Intermediate Algebra_Level 2_1.json.correct_solution: By the Integer Root Theorem, the possible integer roots are all the divisors of 11 (including negative divisors), so they are $\boxed{-11, -1, 1, 11}.$

generated_solutions.gemini-1.5-flash: By the Integer Root Theorem, any integer root of this polynomial must divide 11.  The divisors of 11 are $\boxed{-11,-1,1,11}$.
